Pupils will officially complete their exams on Tuesday when they write the final design &amp; agricultural management practice paper. CAPE TOWN - The marking of matric exam scripts will commence this week.The class of 2016 will officially complete their exams on Tuesday when they write their final design and agricultural management practice papers.The majority of matriculants finished their schooling careers on Monday when they wrote Afrikaans paper 3.The Western Cape Education MEC's spokesperson, Jessica Shelver, says the exams have gone smoothly. The matric exams have run smoothly thus far with no reports of any leaks in the Western Cape. Marking is due to start on Wednesday with 3,881 markers marking the papers in the province. (Edited by Neo Koza)